metadata.name: cold embrace #27
metadata.description:
'cold embrace' is a depiction of a city embraced by a blizzard. Despite the harshness of a snowstorm, there is beauty to be found in the accumulation of snow atop otherwise bare structures.

Infinite variations guarantee a unique scene. 
4 colour palettes of varying rarities.
Utilizes 3 methods of randomness (Gaussian distribution, uniform distribution and Perlin noise).

800x800
100% made with code (using p5.js).

metadata.name: gimme all your love #120
metadata.description: Sometimes we feel so lost that we look for any way to find the ground beneath our feet again. Sometimes we try to feel something through other people, through looks, words, touches. This is a temporary cure, which sooner or later will stop helping.

metadata.name: Begin Again #34
metadata.description:
Find a path, color it, and begin again.
The process may seem simple, but it is anything but. 
An artificial intelligence algorithm is used to find and color the paths in this collection.
Made by p5.js
press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: Megacosm #8
metadata.description:
Megacosm is an attempt to reproduce my approach to physical painting in the digital realm, allowing room for spontaneity and freedom of expression. While the algorithm is ultimately in control it is also, in a sense, free.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save a high-resolution version of the image

Made in p5js
Created January 2023
By John Ryan

metadata.name: MEDUSA #134
metadata.description:
Medusa is a generative piece playing with noise, cosinus/sinus functions and lines.  The radius, frequency and amplitude of each lines are generated for each token, along with the color theme and the lines's count. Some rare items are available.

 Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Amalfi (Italia).

metadata.name: Mar de lã #151
metadata.description:
"Once upon a time, in a land far, far away, there was a magical kingdom known for its beautiful landscapes and mystical creatures. The kingdom was ruled by a kind and fair queen, who loved nothing more than to spend her days exploring the vast and varied terrain of her realm.

One day, the queen was wandering through a particularly cold and snowy region of the kingdom when she came upon a strange sight. Instead of snow, the ground was covered with soft, fluffy balls of wool, as if the earth itself had been transformed into a giant ball of yarn.

The queen was fascinated by this curious phenomenon, and she decided to follow the trail of wool to see where it led. After walking for some time, she came upon a beautiful lake, the surface of which was frozen solid. But instead of ice, the lake was made entirely of woolen fibers, swirling and twirling in the gentle breeze.

The queen marveled at the sight, and she couldn't help but reach out and touch the soft, velvety surface of the woolen lake. As she did, she felt a warmth and comfort wash over her, as if the wool were alive and pulsing with energy.

Over the years, the queen visited the woolen lake often, always feeling a sense of peace and contentment when she was near it. And as the years went by, the people of the kingdom began to flock to the woolen lake, seeking the same sense of warmth and comfort that the queen had found.

The woolen lake became a beloved and sacred place in the kingdom, and it was known throughout the land as the "mar de lã" - the sea of wool. And so it remained, a magical and mystical place that brought joy and happiness to all who visited."
_AI GPT

Made with <3 and p5.js

metadata.name: GRAVITATE #50
metadata.description:
Each piece in this collection is made from the simple concept of layering grids of circles. The varying grid sizes, circle sizes, positions and colors combine to create interesting dithering effects. There are seven color palettes in the algorithm and these range from low contrast, muted palettes (e.g. Mystic Sands) to high contrast, super saturated palettes (e.g. Inferno).

- - -

GRAVITATE is my first generative art collection and was made using only p5.js.

- - -

Commands:
Press `1` to save a low-res PNG 1200x1800
Press `2` to save a high-res PNG 4800x7200

Note that it may take up to 10secs for the image render to complete.
